properties.description: Approximately 900 km of primary backbone electro-optical cable have been installed from the Shore Station to the seven Primary Node locations spanning the Juan de Fuca Plate. The cable provides power (10 kV DC, up to 8 A) and communications (10 Gb/s) via fiber-optics and copper between the Primary Nodes and the Shore Station in Pacific City, Oregon.
properties.name: Backbone Cable
